headline: France demands 1.7 bn euros in payroll taxes from Uber: media report
summary:
Ride-sharing group Uber has been told by French authorities that it owes 1.7 billion euros ($2 billion) in unpaid payroll taxes, according to a media report Monday.  According to Revue21, Urssaf estimates that Uber avoided 1.2 billion euros in payroll taxes, to which it added 512 million euros in "recovery surcharges".
bj-hrc/abb/lth/gv/sbk
